<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,310,1353,1379]" box="[189,310,1353,1379]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1353,1379]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1353,1379]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,1404,1906]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Body densely covered with long and narrow scales with marginal spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov D. V." box="[1041,1218,1404,1431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="589 - 604" refId="ref8279" refString="Logunov D. V. 1995. The genus Mogrus (Araneae: Salticidae) of central Asia. European Journal of Entomology 92: 589 - 604." type="journal article" year="1995">Logunov 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Prosoma with elevated and broader ocular field. Posterior prosoma steeper. Chelicerae with two fused promarginal and one retromarginal tooth (
<bibRefCitation author="Andreeva E. M. &amp; Kononenko A. P. &amp; Proszynski J." box="[477,726,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="85 - 104" refId="ref7647" refString="Andreeva E. M., Kononenko A. P. &amp; Proszynski J. 1981. Remarks on genus Mogrus Simon, 1882 (Araneae, Salticidae). Annales Zoologici 36: 85 - 104." type="journal article" year="1981">
Andreeva 
<emphasis box="[599,657,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
1981
</bibRefCitation>
). Oval abdomen with a dark, median serrated longitudinal band in males. Palp with narrowed and curved cymbium. RTA moderately long, slightly curved apically, shape variable. Embolus originating perpendicularly to bulbus, bending and running parallel to bulbus margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Proszynski J." box="[287,489,1602,1629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref8380" refString="Proszynski J. 2016. Monograph of the Salticidae (Araneae) of the World 1995 - 2014. Chapter II: Global species database of Salticidae [online]. Available from http: // www. peckhamia. com / salticidae / index. html [accessed 1 Jul. 2016]." type="url" year="2016">Prószyński 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Pars pendula and truncus well-developed (
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov D. V." box="[1006,1184,1602,1629]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="589 - 604" refId="ref8279" refString="Logunov D. V. 1995. The genus Mogrus (Araneae: Salticidae) of central Asia. European Journal of Entomology 92: 589 - 604." type="journal article" year="1995">Logunov 1995</bibRefCitation>
: figs 4, 43). Distal sclerite of embolus easily visible and distal hematodocha connected to terminal apophysis (
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov D. V." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="589 - 604" refId="ref8279" refString="Logunov D. V. 1995. The genus Mogrus (Araneae: Salticidae) of central Asia. European Journal of Entomology 92: 589 - 604." type="journal article" year="1995">Logunov 1995</bibRefCitation>
: figs 41–43). Bulbus broad oval or nearly rounded, with striking lateral or basal protuberance (
<bibRefCitation author="Andreeva E. M. &amp; Kononenko A. P. &amp; Proszynski J." box="[197,454,1721,1747]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="85 - 104" refId="ref7647" refString="Andreeva E. M., Kononenko A. P. &amp; Proszynski J. 1981. Remarks on genus Mogrus Simon, 1882 (Araneae, Salticidae). Annales Zoologici 36: 85 - 104." type="journal article" year="1981">
Andreeva 
<emphasis box="[322,383,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
1981
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Proszynski J." box="[469,671,1721,1748]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref8380" refString="Proszynski J. 2016. Monograph of the Salticidae (Araneae) of the World 1995 - 2014. Chapter II: Global species database of Salticidae [online]. Available from http: // www. peckhamia. com / salticidae / index. html [accessed 1 Jul. 2016]." type="url" year="2016">Prószyński 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Sperm duct broad and simple. Epigyne oval, with a pair of narrow subparallel depressions in the anterior half connected anteriorly and resembling a horseshoe, with copulatory openings at their posterior end (
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov D. V." box="[702,880,1800,1827]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="589 - 604" refId="ref8279" refString="Logunov D. V. 1995. The genus Mogrus (Araneae: Salticidae) of central Asia. European Journal of Entomology 92: 589 - 604." type="journal article" year="1995">Logunov 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Proszynski J." box="[894,1095,1800,1827]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref8380" refString="Proszynski J. 2016. Monograph of the Salticidae (Araneae) of the World 1995 - 2014. Chapter II: Global species database of Salticidae [online]. Available from http: // www. peckhamia. com / salticidae / index. html [accessed 1 Jul. 2016]." type="url" year="2016">Prószyński 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Broad and membranous insemination ducts, rounded sac-like spermathecae with thick walls. Conspicuous, short accessory glands.
</paragraph>
